{"timestamp":"00:09:17.337","source":"Browser","level":"ERROR","message":"The final argument passed to %s changed size between renders. The order and size of this array must remain constant.\n\nPrevious: %s\nIncoming: %s useEffect [15, One of the first lessons chess teaches is patience. Beginners often believe the goal is to attack as quickly as possible, launching pieces forward in search of a fast checkmate. But experienced players understand that real progress in a chess game is often invisible. Improving a single piece, controlling a key square, or preventing an opponent’s plan can matter more than a direct attack.\r\nPatience in chess means accepting that not every move changes the evaluation immediately. Sometimes you must maneuver slowly, waiting for weaknesses to appear. Strong players are comfortable with quiet positions because they understand that pressure accumulates over time.\r\nInterestingly, this lesson extends far beyond the chessboard. In life, just like in chess, rushing decisions often creates new problems. Careful preparation and timing usually lead to better outcomes than impulsive action. Chess rewards those who can wait — and punishes those who cannot., Patience in Chess] [15, One of the first lessons chess teaches is patience. Beginners often believe the goal is to attack as quickly as possible, launching pieces forward in search of a fast checkmate. But experienced players understand that real progress in a chess game is often invisible. Improving a single piece, controlling a key square, or preventing an opponent’s plan can matter more than a direct attack.\r\nPatience in chess means accepting that not every move changes the evaluation immediately. Sometimes you must maneuver slowly, waiting for weaknesses to appear. Strong players are comfortable with quiet positions because they understand that pressure accumulates over time.\r\nInterestingly, this lesson extends far beyond the chessboard. In life, just like in chess, rushing decisions often creates new problems. Careful preparation and timing usually lead to better outcomes than impulsive action. Chess rewards those who can wait — and punishes those who cannot., Patience in Chess, /api/uploads/posts/1774778055055-f0b2f045928abaef.png]"}
